			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1333">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Alan Craig&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;Push Here for Tears&rdquo; [January 2008] resonated with me. I, too, find animal suffering impossible to bear, and I don&rsquo;t have any more answers than he does as to why this is so. I grieve over human suffering, too, but if animals are being hurt, I have to turn off the <span class="smallcaps">TV</span> or shut the book. Their misery feels like my own.</p>

<p>I do rescue animals (I once tried to steal a beagle that was being neglected), and I have felt the joy of placing abandoned pets in loving homes, but I don&rsquo;t volunteer at a shelter because I fear I&rsquo;d be incapacitated by the loneliness of the caged, often doomed animals.</p>

<p>Craig&rsquo;s essay has encouraged me to look for some insight into the roots of this &ldquo;malady&rdquo; he and I share.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Nancy Ferguson<br>Dallas, Texas</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
